Product Id: Survey of Labour and Income Dynamics
Source: Income Statistics Division, Statistics Canada

Data quality indicators are based on the coefficient of variation (CV) and number of observations. Quality indicators indicate the following: A - Excellent (CV between 0% and 2%); B - Very good (CV between 2% and 4%); C - Good (CV between 4% and 8%); D - Acceptable (CV between 8% and 16%); E - Use with caution (CV greater than or equal to 16%).
Refers to a male-female married or common-law couple where at least one of the husband or wife earns an income.
Includes families where spouses had equal earnings.
Data for this census metropolitan area are available only from 1998.
Selected income time series from CANSIM 202* tables are now available in CANSIM 206* tables.
